WASHINGTON The National
Labor Relations Board announced
1t would appoint the first Negro
hearing examiner in the Federal
Government. He Is Arthur Chris
TOPPER Jr., labor board at
torney.


Board hearing examiners
whose formal title is trial ex-
aminer conduct hearings and is
sue decisions, renewable by the
board, in unfair labor practice
cases.


Christopher, 81 years old, has
served as labor board lawyer
since 1916. He is law school
graduate of Howard University.
